🔹 Step 1: Login to Azure Portal

Open browser and visit:

Microsoft Azure Portal

Login using your Microsoft account.

🔹 Step 2: Create Azure Web App

After logging into Azure Portal:

Go to:

Create a Resource → Web App
Fill the Required Details

Enter the following information:

Field	Example Value
Subscription	Your Azure Subscription
Resource Group	Create new or select existing
App Name	mywebappdemo
Publish	Code
Runtime Stack	Java / Tomcat / Java Version
Operating System	Linux or Windows
Region	Central India
Configure App Service Plan

Azure automatically creates or selects an App Service Plan.

Click:

Review + Create

Then click:

Create

Deployment will start.

🔹 Step 3: Verify Web App Creation

After deployment completes:

Click:

Go to Resource

You will see the Azure Web App dashboard.

Copy the application URL:

https://<app-name>.azurewebsites.net

Open it in browser to verify the Web App is running.

🔹 Step 4: Create Azure Key Vault

In Azure Portal:

Go to:

Create a Resource → Key Vault
Enter Key Vault Details

Fill the following fields:

Field	Example Value
Subscription	Your Azure Subscription
Resource Group	Existing or New
Key Vault Name	mykeyvaultdemo
Region	Central India
Pricing Tier	Standard

Click:

Review + Create

Then click:

Create

Azure will deploy the Key Vault.

🔹 Step 5: Add Secret to Key Vault

Open the created Key Vault.

Navigate to:

Secrets → Generate/Import

Enter:

Field	Example
Upload Options	Manual
Name	DB_PASSWORD
Value	admin123

Click:

Create

Secret is now securely stored inside Azure Key Vault.

🔹 Step 6: Verify Key Vault

Open:

Key Vault → Secrets

Verify that the secret is successfully added.
